<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-88-0090 </DOCNO><TEXT>The article deals with 4 complex issues: 1) Promotional purpose and profitabilityconsiderations in securing the safety of nuclear facilities under aspectsof hazard abatement and prevention, hazard analysis, dimension of hazardcontrol, residual risk minimization; 2) Binding effect in partial licensingand scope of discretion in denying licenses; 3) Immediate enforcementof licenses under the Atomic Energy Law; 4) Consistency of direct finalstorage of spent fuel elements with the Atomic Energy Law. The articleconcludes with a brief discussion of protective measures against sabotageand of making the Code of Nuclear Technology into a law, i.e. its statutorycodification.</TEXT></DOC>